				<div class="col-lg-4">				    
					<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="~/Content/Photos/earlyRelationship.jpg" /></p>
				</div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 herstory">
                    <p>Summer 2011 I had just randomly moved to Nashville, started a new job, and moved in with my best friend Molly. 2 weeks later it was Labor Day weekend; not knowing a lot of people at work, and Molly being my only friend (and pregnant at the time), I decided to sign up on Match.com. Figured I could use the “new in town” excuse to get at least a couple of dates, and have someone show me the sites. After I signed up, I got a few responses from guys, but none grabbed my interest, except one: Aaron. He actually wrote a paragraph, a conversation, had questions, and said more than “sup girl.” I responded. We wrote long emails back and forth throughout the week, and knowing the upcoming weekend was a holiday weekend, with no plans, we decided to go out. He picked me up, we hopped from Bosco’s on 21st, to Jacksons, to Flying Saucer, and eventually ending on Broadway. That first date lasted 14 hours!</p>
                    <p>Many dates to come after were similar – lasting 12 hours, all day, all weekend…etc. We’ve been together ever since. Aaron is the only one I've been with the whole time I've lived in Nashville and have loved every minute of it. He is my best friend, the love of my life. He makes me laugh and smile all the time, while laughing at my jokes. He’s always up for any adventures that I want to do -- ranging from skydiving, para-sailing, hang gliding, traveling all over the country to just hanging out and binge watching great TV shows at home. I’m excited for our next big adventure together: Marriage!</p>
                </div>
			</div>
