            </div>
            <div class="row text-center">
                <h3>Hers</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="row text-justify herstory">
                <p>Night of the Proposal: It was our 2 year anniversary, and sticking with tradition, we were going out to another fun, new, fancy restaurant. We have turned Labor Day weekend into our anniversary trips, and having just come back from Charleston, SC, we kept the anniversary day pretty low key (or so I thought). Side note… we give each other presents all the time! Birthdays, holidays, anniversaries, just cause. I had bought and wrapped some fun toys for him and kept them on the dining room table days leading up the anniversary. By the day of, I noticed there weren't any for me yet – which wasn't unusual, he would order some late or pick them up on the way home. I met him at the restaurant, still knowing that morning there weren't any presents on the table for me, and when I didn't see a box popping out of his pocket when he walked up, I figured my presents would come later (I had been hinting at wanting a bike rack for my car for weeks!). We chose that particular restaurant (Bricktops) because I had heard their deviled eggs were amazing, and being in love with deviled eggs, I needed to eat these suckers! We sat down, ordered champagne and deviled eggs, talking about random things. The eggs came and I inhaled them! In between bites, I was asking Aaron what he wanted to do after dinner … did he want to go home open presents, go bowling, go get drinks…etc. We decided on opening presents first then figure out plans (especially since I was excited for him to open up his toys, and knew he’d want to play with them). He then said, “I’m going to give you your present now.” As I took another bite of the delicious deviled eggs, my mind instantly thought, “What? Really? If it’s a bike rack I’m going to have to carry it in the restaurant”… not remembering that he came empty handed to the restaurant. He then pulls out the ring and hands it to me!! BAM! KA-BOOM! So shiny and sparkly and the most beautiful thing I’d ever seen in my life… all with a mouth full of eggs. I instantly started to cry, turned bright red, and finished chewing. After the shock and surprise wore off, I realized I hadn't even given an answer. I blurted “YES!” It was the most perfect ring, more beautiful than I could have imagined. And he made sure it had rubies, my birth stone and favorite gem. Needless to say, after that, I didn't have an appetite.</p>
                <p>It's been fun planning our wedding together, and I can't wait to share the big day with family and friends!</p>
